HEADWORD: Feeble-minded
<hw>Fee"ble-mind"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Weak in
intellectual power; wanting firmness or constancy; irresolute;
vacillating; imbecile.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧comfort the
<xex>feeble-minded</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>1 Thess. v. 14.</au></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Fee"ble-mind"ed*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

